<subSubSection id="C358655E861F6B39FED486C0FC40F4A3" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861F6B39FED486C0FC40F4A3" blockId="13.[218,1203,2740,3194]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
<materialsCitation id="3B2A3C88861F6B39FED486C0FC4FF4A3" location="Glenbawn Dam" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" specimenCount="3">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861F6B39FED486C0FD1AF547" bold="true" box="[268,640,2740,2780]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Additional material.</emphasis>
30 additional specimens of G. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861F6B39FF048697FEC6F491" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" box="[220,348,2787,2826]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Glabrocingulum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="obesum">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861F6B39FF048697FEC6F491" box="[220,348,2787,2826]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">obesum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Y00, 1988 were recovered from the 
<typeStatus id="54F98877861F6B39FC3A8697FBB3F491" box="[994,1065,2787,2826]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
locality and east of 
<location id="8E9D600E861F6B39FE678765FD4BF4A3" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EB87C3861F6B39FE668422FD7EF3E1:8E9D600E861F6B39FE678765FD4BF4A3" box="[447,721,2833,2872]" name="Glenbawn Dam" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Glenbawn Dam</location>
(Locality 30)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861F6B39FED3874BFD7EF3E1" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861F6B39FED3874BFD7EF3E1" blockId="13.[218,1203,2740,3194]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861F6B39FED3874BFE23F4FD" bold="true" box="[267,441,2879,2918]" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</emphasis>
The figllred specimens (PI. 6 figs 6, 9, 10) appear to be immature. The specimens (PI. 6 figs 4, 5) have straight whorl profiles with smaller pleural angle, coarser ornamentation and smaller umbilicus, which appears to be relatively mature. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861F6B39FF028051FC76F3D7" authority="(Dun &amp; Benson)" baseAuthorityName="Dun &amp; Benson" box="[218,1004,3109,3148]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Glabrocingulum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="13" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ornatum">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861F6B39FF028051FD03F3D7" box="[218,665,3109,3148]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="76">Glabrocingulum ornatum</emphasis>
(Dun &amp; Benson)
</taxonomicName>
in having smaller and low-spired shell.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
